text: The Veerse Gat or Veeregat was the sea channel between Walcheren and Noord- Beveland islands in Zeeland in the Netherlands. In 1961 as part of the Delta Plan it was blocked off and made into an inland lake called Veerse Meer. ==References== Category:Bodies of water of the Netherlands Category:Channels of Europe Category:Delta Works Category:History of Zeeland Category:Goes Category:Middelburg Category:Noord-Beveland Category:Veere
